*** IMPORTANT: The C Object System requires GNU make 3.81 or higher ***

Compilation/tests/[un]install:
------------------------------

# in the source tree
cd path-to-cos
make [target] [INSTALL=path-to-prefix]

# ouside the source tree
cd path-to-build
make -f path-to-cos/Makefile [target] [INSTALL=path-to-prefix]

# possible targets
tests, install, uninstall

# default install
INSTALL=/usr

Makefile examples:
------------------

# distribution
path-to-cos/Makefile

# library
path-to-cos/CosBase/Makefile

# program
path-to-cos/CosBase/tests/Makefile

# examples
path-to-cos/CosBase/examples/ex??/Makefile

Debugging makefiles:
--------------------

make [target] SHOW=yes TRACE=yes

# debug flags
SHOW  will show the commands run
TRACE will show the value of important variables

Code examples:
--------------

path-to-cos/CosBase/examples

Supported platforms:
--------------------

note: platforms name are detected using the posix command "uname -s"

the list of supported platforms are in the directory
path-to-cos/CosBase/include/cos/cfg/

porting on Unixes/Posix compliant platform should be easy
porting on Windows requires some Posix-like environment (e.g. Mingw, Cygwin)

Tested platforms:
-----------------

# Architectures
Linux Ubuntu 8.04 and 8.10 (Debian) on i386   (32-bit) Core2 Duo
Linux Ubuntu 8.04 and 8.10 (Debian) on x86_64 (64-bit) Core2 Duo
Linux SLC 4.0              (RedHat) on x86_64 (64-bit) Quad Xeon
Mac OS X Leopard           (Darwin) on x86_64 (64-bit) Core2 Duo

# Compilers
gcc 3.2.3, 3.4.6, 4.1.2, 4.2.4, 4.3.2

Documentation:
--------------

path-to-prefix/share/doc/cos/

